div.p: Transcribing this text for papyri.info required a number of departures from the critical edition of Azzarello 2019, principally as regards the handling of the small oblique strokes (or ‚Äòticks‚Äô) that accompany whole numbers and fractions on papyri. Where Azzarello‚Äôs text supplements these (if they are missing), and expunges them (if they were added superfluously), papyri.info is unable to render these ‚Äòticks‚Äô within angled or curly brackets. The text transcribed here, therefore, is that of the papyrus: where a tick is present on the papyrus ‚Äì even in error ‚Äì it is encoded; when one is absent it is not, even if the number is a fraction and would normally be expected to include one. The exception to this practice is where ticks are marked on the papyrus beside each digit in a double or triple-digit fraction (e.g., col. i.4 where Œª¬¥ Œµ¬¥ = 1/35): in such cases, papyri.info can only render a single tick even if two appear on the papyrus (ŒªŒµ¬¥ instead of Œª¬¥ Œµ¬¥). The commentary notes other curiosities involving ticks.
The first two columns are preserved by SB 20 15071; the rest are on P.Mich. 3 146.
